results.name: Sum of the divisors of n that are not divisible by 5.
reference: B. C. Berndt, Ramanujan's Notebooks Part III, Springer-Verlag, see p. 463 Entry 4(i).
link: Seiichi Manyama, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
formula: a(n) is multiplicative with a(5^e) = 1, a(p^e) = (p^(e+1)-1)/(p-1) otherwise.
L.g.f.: log(Product_{k>=1} (1 - x^(5*k))/(1 - x^k)) = Sum_{n>=1} a(n)*x^n/n. - _Ilya Gutkovskiy_, Mar 14 2018
mathematica: f[p_, e_] := If[p == 5, 1, (p^(e+1)-1)/(p-1)]; a[1] = 1; a[n_] := Times @@ f @@@ FactorInteger[n]; Array[a, 100] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Sep 17 2020 *)
xref: Cf. A035207 (number of divisors of n that are not divisible by 5).
results.author: _Michael Somos_, Feb 04 2006
